  "body": "\nFederation starts from substrate sovereignty.\n\nAnother substrate may import, map, compare, or reject data, but it must not silently overwrite [provenance](/node/provenance), collapse disagreement, or erase local moderation decisions.\n\nThe canonical rule is simple: merge by adding structure, not by destroying context.\n",
